snippet.textDisplay:
This is a smaller version of when my friend bought what he thought was a small abandoned building and lot that was surrounded by fence w barbwire to start a shop and store cars & bikes. Bought it from City Auction for unpaid taxes around $7000.00. When they took possession and entered the shop they found a late 80’s tow truck with ALL the gear and extra dolly’s, chains, strapping, etc ($5000/$8000). Then under a HEAVY cover in the corner was a 1970’s Cadillac coupe convertible in PERFECT condition with 2500 miles on it. Someone had put boxes of mothballs in the trunk, engine, and the floorboards to keep out the rats. Boxes were empty but the mothball smell lingered enough and it worked. We flagged down a local cop and explained what we found. He was cool and HONEST by telling us “If I run these VIN #’s now and they comeback stolen I’m required to tow them out of here. You ‘might’ want to go to DMV and just apply for ‘lost titles’ and if there aren’t ANY claims/flags on the titles they are LEGALLY yours...” He didn’t have to give us that “option” but it was VERY cool for him to tell us that “option” Because that’s what we did. Both tow truck and Caddie fired up fine and just needed good cleaning and regular maintenance. We sold the Cadillac for 45k and it paid for WHOLE PLACE plus ALL the repairs to the car lifts hydraulics, new epoxy floor, oil burning heater system, etc.
Anyway, it’s going to be interesting to see what else these guys “find” along the way here with their new “playground”...👍👍

snippet.textDisplay: Love the videos, keep 'em coming. I have an off topic question. since you have way more experience with go pros, i need some advice and tips. I drive a western star big rig that keeps shredding the fan belt. We have changed everything on the front as far as the accessory drive including the dampener. it made it 2 weeks after that and shredded another one when we thought it was fixed and has now shred it's 6th belt in 4 months. no one can figure out why. I would like to mount a go pro under the hood pointed at the serpentine belt to catch it in action and maybe that will give us a clue as to why this keeps happening. I read that go pros only record about 4.25 hrs with a 32 gig. I need more hrs. buy the biggest memory card I can find the fits a go pro, it's going to be under hood and dark so a light would be good here. how many hrs can you do on one with a good enough quality to catch that moment and at what quality?
